Template: booktype/server-setup
Type: select
_Choices: yes please, no thanks
_Default: yes please
_Description: Set up server automatically?
 This script can perform automatic configuration of a default instance, so that
 you can begin using Booktype directly after installation.
 .
 Choose 'yes please' and the script will ask for details in order to set up
 the Booktype instance and create a virtual host configuration for Apache.
 .
 If you choose 'no thanks', that's no problem. You're welcome to set it up
 however you like. The files in /etc/booktype/ may come in handy.
 .

Template: booktype/database-name
Type: string
Default: 
_Description: Name of the Booktype database
 Enter the name of the database for Booktype to use.
 .

Template: booktype/database-user
Type: string
Default:                       
_Description: Booktype database owner username
 Enter the username of the Booktype database owner.
 .

Template: booktype/database-password
Type: password
Default:             
_Description: Password for the Booktype database
 Enter the password for the database which Booktype will use.
 .

Template: booktype/database-host
Type: string
Default: localhost
_Description: Booktype database host
 Enter the hostname of the machine serving the Booktype database. 
 .

Template: booktype/database-port
Type: string
Default: 5432          
_Description: Booktype database port
 Enter the port number that your database server uses. The default for
 PostgreSQL database servers is 5432.
 .

Template: booktype/admin-name
Type: string
_Default: Booktype Administrator
_Description: Name of the Booktype server administrator
 Enter the name of the system administrator for your Booktype users to contact.
 .

Template: booktype/admin-email
Type: string
Default: root@localhost
_Description: Email address of the Booktype server administrator
 Enter the email address of the system administrator for your Booktype users to
 contact.
 .

Template: booktype/booktype-site-name 
Type: string
_Default: Booktype Site
_Description: Name of the default Booktype instance
 Enter the name of the default Booktype instance, which will be shown in the
 user interface template for that instance.
 .

Template: booktype/this-booktype-server
Type: string
Default: 
_Description: Domain name of the default Booktype instance
 Enter the domain name of the default Booktype instance. The DNS record for
 this domain name must resolve to the Apache server running on this machine,
 for example:
 .
 booktype.example.com
 .

Template: booktype/report-email-user
Type: string
Default: 
_Description: Report email user
 Enter the 'From' address for Booktype to use when sending management reports.
 .

Template: booktype/email-host
Type: string
Default: localhost
_Description: Email host 
 Enter the mail server for Booktype to use when sending email.
 .

Template: booktype/email-port
Type: string
Default: 25
_Description: Email port
 Enter the SMTP port for Booktype to use when sending email.
 .

Template: booktype/default-publisher
Type: string
_Default: Unknown
_Description: Default publisher
 Enter the name of the default publisher for new books.
 .

Template: booktype/redis-host
Type: string
Default: localhost
_Description: Redis host
 Enter the Redis server hostname. For a typical installation, you can use the
 default of 'localhost'.
 .

Template: booktype/redis-port
Type: string
Default: 6379
_Description: Redis port
 Enter the port number that your Redis server uses. The default port is 6379.
 .

Template: booktype/redis-db
Type: string
Default: 0
_Description: Redis database number
 Enter the number of the Redis database. If you only have one application using
 the Redis server, this value can be the default of zero.
 .

Template: booktype/redis-password
Type: password
Default: None     
_Description: Redis password
 Enter the Redis password, if your server requires one. The default is 'None'.
 .

Template: booktype/time-zone
Type: string
Default: Europe/Berlin     
_Description: Default instance time zone
 Enter the time zone for your default Booktype instance.
 .

Template: booktype/interface-language     
Type: string  
Default: en-us
_Description: Default instance interface language
 Enter the interface language code for your default Booktype instance.
 .
